description: Sky Master by Washington Bud Company is a strain born and bred in the heart of the Pacific Northwest. The sativa-dominant offspring of Blue Dream and Master Kush, Sky Master inherits their tried-and-true effects which give consumers a pleasurable jolt of uplifting cerebral energy that translates to warm, functional relaxation. Thanks to its uplifting buzz, this floral, pine-scented strain lends well to achy and active cannabis consumers on the go.

highlightedReviews.text: 💚💚💚😍😍😍 OMFG 💚💚💚 I love this strain!!! I tried it several months ago in concentrate form (Avitas cartridge 1g), it has a great cerebral high that feels absolutely amazing and knocks out pain, fatigue, anxiety, stress, nasal congestion, nausea for me 😁😎 please give it a try when you can find it 😎😁 freakin awesome strain 💚💚💚

Wow.  I was looking for a strain with lots of cerebral, even psychedelic, effects and I definitely found it here. I searched my nearest dispensaries for either Blue Dream or Master Kush, since they are said to have the type of high I was looking for. Couldn't find either one in stock at my usual places, so I took a chance on this hybrid of the two.

I'm a moderate to heavy user (every other night or every third night is typical for me) and I don't go in for an easy body high or a light experience.  If I don't feel like I'm existing in multiple dimensions at once, I don't see the point, so I really go all in. All that's to say that I'm no stranger to getting high and I have a pretty good handle on how much it takes to get me to the right level.

The first time I used Sky Master, I tried three or four puffs on my vaporizer and it quickly launched me straight past "the right level" and into a whole new experience. This was not necessarily a good thing, as I was in an unfamiliar place at the time and wasn't well prepared for a really trippy session. Well, as I had been searching for a strain with strong psychedelic effects, I knew immediately that I had found it with Sky Master. I often  combine vaping with a 10-mg edible, too, so I can keep it going for longer, but in vaping less than I usually do and using no edibles, I was experiencing things cannabis had never done to me before. It was easily more potent an experience than my first-ever time using cannabis, so...yeah. This strain means business. I had to talk myself out of believing that my mind was going to totally shatter and I wouldn't come out of the Sky Master experience with my personality intact.

Thankfully, that was not the case. I'm just fine, and since then Sky Master and I have become very good friends. I definitely need to use a lot less of this strain than I do any other strain I've tried, but the high is pretty spectacular if you like a very "up," creative, mind-expanding experience. It's such a unique feeling; hard to describe, as all I can really think to call it is consciousness- and awareness-expanding to some distant reaches. This one will be on my list of favorite strains for good, I think! Kudos to Sky Master's breeder for a real botanical achievement.

I still haven't tried either of the parent strains yet...darn.

name: Sky Master
